You Collected all the Pieces of my plan, THANK YOU!!! now Shay's rebellion can go ahead and myself and other veterans can fight for the money owed to us
As you completed ‘Help The Rebellion’ you can put your name on the wall of fame, this is available on the website, if you do not wish to do this press exit
Add Name To Wall Of Fame And Exit
Congratulations for completing "Help The Rebellion", if you click download you will receive a certificate, if you do not wish to do this press exit

Greetings,

My name is Captain Daniel Shay, I am a soldier, farmer and a recently turned revolutionary, outraged at the laws that Massachusetts is passing to tax poorer farmers like myself. 

Its here at Conkey's Tavern that we plan to show the courts we won’t be taken advantage of, our first step is ... where did I put the revolution plan?

Ah haha,

My name is James Bowdoin, charged with putting down Daniel Shay’s foolish rebellion. I’ve stolen his plan, cut it into parts and hidden the parts all over American History ...

What did James Bowdoin say... all over American History, well this rebellion isn't going ahead without my plan,

Luckily I know some collectors, Dallas Pratt and John Judkyn, who have artefacts from all over America, they house them in the American Musuem ... hey thats right here! I've got a note of the artefacts James hid pieces of my plan in, would you be able to take a look around and see if you can find them, I'm sure James has put puzzles in place to make it difficult but I bet you can do it!

If you need any help through the game click on me and Ill see what I can do, Good Luck!
Well Done! Stopping the wheel on the year this spinning wheel was made opened a secret compartment containing a piece of my plan
To continue, click on the piece
There are 6 puzzles on the board, they will all require information from different Period Rooms to complete, once completed you will receive a piece of Daniel Shay's Rebellion Plan
In order to play a puzzle, click on its picture on the notice board
Once you complete all 6 puzzles and therefore get all 6 pieces of Daniel Shay's Rebellion Plan you can exit the game and put your name on the wall of fame
There is no time limit so take your time exploring the museum
If you get stuck you can use the 'Hint' button to help you
